---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const pageTitle = 'Contact Astrolify Load Test 01 20260522-042729105'
const pageDescription = 'Contact routes for editorial feedback, business questions, and communication about Astrolify Load Test 01 20260522-042729105.'
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <article class="ac-generated-page">
    <header class="ac-generated-page__header">
      <p class="ac-generated-page__eyebrow">Pages</p>
      <h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
      <p>{pageDescription}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="ac-generated-page__section">
      <h2>How to reach the publication</h2>
      <p>Use [CONTACT_EMAIL] for general enquiries, editorial notes, and messages that do not need a public reply.</p>
      <p>If a newsletter is added later, it should be kept separate from general contact requests.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="ac-generated-page__section">
      <h2>Which enquiries are appropriate</h2>
      <p>Use the published email route for general enquiries, corrections, or messages that do not need a formal support queue.</p>
      <p>The contact page is best suited to questions about support requests, account questions, partnership conversations, and product-related enquiries.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="ac-generated-page__section">
      <h2>What readers should expect</h2>
      <p>Responses, when they are provided, will depend on the type of enquiry and the availability of the editorial team.</p>
      <p>No guaranteed response window is implied unless the site later publishes one as part of a real support or business workflow.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="ac-generated-page__section">
      <h2>How messages are handled</h2>
      <p>Contact messages should be treated as operational communication rather than as public content.</p>
      <p>If more formal handling is required later, the site can add a specific retention or routing policy without changing the basic page structure.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="ac-generated-page__section">
      <h2>Editorial contact and corrections</h2>
      <p>For publishing sites, this page also acts as the usual place for corrections, tip-offs, partnership enquiries, and requests related to published material.</p>
      <p>If contact routes change later, this page should be updated before the old route is removed from the site.</p>
    </section>
    <aside class="ac-generated-page__notice">
      <p>This starter page is generated as a baseline and should be reviewed and customized before being relied on as production legal or business copy.</p>
    </aside>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .ac-generated-page {
    width: min(100% - 2rem, 48rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .ac-generated-page__header,
  .ac-generated-page__section,
  .ac-generated-page__notice {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .ac-generated-page__eyebrow {
    color: rgb(var(--ac-primary));
    font-weight: var(--ac-font-semibold);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .ac-generated-page h1,
  .ac-generated-page h2 {
    color: var(--ac-text);
  }

  .ac-generated-page p {
    color: var(--ac-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--ac-leading-relaxed);
  }

  .ac-generated-page__notice {
    border: 0.0625rem solid var(--ac-border-color);
    border-radius: var(--ac-rounded-xl);
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--ac-bg-subtle);
  }
</style>
